725829f-a.title: Queens: 122nd Street - Jamaica Avenue
725829f-a.text:
) 12nd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Jamaica
Avenue, showing an aaditbrium. One of the signs reads:
"Meeting Rooas for Rent.' The wooded plot together with
the auditorium was known as Columbia Park in 1909 and was,
in all probability, a local picnic ground. It may have
been C. Annbruster's Richmond Hill Rotel of 1891, on the
Brooklyn & Jamaica Plank Road (now Jamaica Avenue), at
Willow Street.
P. L. Sperr  Augost 22, 1932

727010f-a.text:
